The remains of Chief of Army Staff, COAS, Ibrahim Attahiru and Muslim officers, who died in the air crash have arrived at the National Mosque, Abuja. Attahiru, as DAILY POST reported on Friday, died together with with his aides and other senior army officers in Kaduna. He died in an air crash at about 6:00p.m on Friday on board military Beechcraft 350 which went down at the Kaduna International Airport, claiming all passengers. The top military officer was in Kaduna on an official trip. DAILY POST gathered that Attahiruâ€™s aides also died in the crash. His body is currently at the National Mosque for the last prayers and burial rites. Video: 